article.description: Colton Weisbrod scored 26 points, Nick Garth added a career-high tying 25 and Josh Nzeakor had a double-double on Wednesday night to help Lamar beat Incarnate Word 90-69 and snap a three-game skid.
article.headline: Weisbrod, Nzeakor help Lamar beat Incarnate Word 90-69
article.linkText: Weisbrod, Nzeakor help Lamar beat Incarnate Word 90-69
article.story: SAN ANTONIO -- Colton Weisbrod scored 26 points, Nick Garth added a career-high tying 25 and Josh Nzeakor had a double-double on Wednesday night to help Lamar beat Incarnate Word 90-69 and snap a three-game skid. Nzeakor finished with 18 points and 12 rebounds, Weisbrod grabbed nine boards and Garth had five assists. Zjori Bosha had 11 points and three steals for Lamar (11-8, 3-3 Southland Conference). Nzeakor made a layup and then a jumper to make it 6-0 and Lamar never trailed. Garth hit a jumper to make it 47-34 going into the break and UIW (5-11, 0-6) trailed by double figures throughout the second half. Charles Brown III had 24 points and Keaton Hervey scored 20 for UIW, which has lost eight in a row. Lamar scored 18 points off 12 UIW turnovers and converted 14 offensive rebounds into 20 second-chance points.
